# Cline Rules for saas-deployer

## Project Overview
TypeScript CLI tool (ESM, Node 18+) automating SaaS deployment: Stripe, databases, auth, email, monitoring, GitHub, Vercel.

## Build & Test
- `npm run build` — tsup -> dist/cli.js
- `npm test` — vitest, 703 tests
- `npm run dev` — tsx src/cli.ts
- `npx tsc --noEmit` — typecheck

## Source Layout
- `src/cli.ts` — Commander entry, 13 commands, global flags (--no-interactive, --dry-run, -y, --verbose)
- `src/commands/` — thin wrappers calling provider.setup() and persisting results
- `src/providers/` — service implementations, each exports a Provider (see types.ts)
- `src/providers/types.ts` — Provider interface: preflight() + setup() -> ProviderResult
- `src/providers/links.ts` — ALL dashboard URLs centralized here
- `src/config/schema.ts` — Zod v2 schema for saas.config.json
- `src/config/store.ts` — loadConfig(), saveConfig(), markStepCompleted()
- `src/config/credentials.ts` — encrypted credential storage (per-machine key)
- `src/config/migrate.ts` — v1->v2 migration, transparent in loadConfig()
- `src/templates/` — framework-specific code as TS string exports (Next.js, Remix, SvelteKit, Nuxt, Astro)
- `src/deploy/` — topological sort + orchestrator
- `src/presets/` — minimal, startup, enterprise
- `src/env/` — EnvManager for .env generation
- `src/ui/` — logger, spinner, prompts (with non-interactive fallback)
- `tests/` — 31 files, 703 tests

## Conventions
- ESM only, `.js` import extensions, no default exports
- Providers return `{ success, configUpdates, envVars, manualSteps }` — never mutate config
- Dashboard URLs only in `src/providers/links.ts`
- Native fetch (no axios), no shell: true in exec
- Secrets piped via stdin, never in CLI args
- Non-interactive: prompts fall back to env vars via isInteractive()
- Build before running CLI tests
